10:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Who Should Choose Which?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The ideal user for each platform differs considerably. Phind is best suited for developers searching for code solutions, replacing Stack Overflow, making it a strong choice if you fall into any of these categories. Qodo, meanwhile, shines for quality focused development teams, automated test generation, which means it may be the better pick if your needs align with those use cases.\n\nFounded in 2022, Phind describes itself as \"AI search engine built for developers.\" Qodo, established in 2022, positions itself as \"AI-powered code integrity and test generation.\" Both platforms have been in the market for a similar duration, giving each ample time to refine their offerings and build a loyal user base."}]]}]
11:["$","div",null,{"className":"verdict-box","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Our Verdict"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"After analyzing all the data, **Qodo** comes out slightly ahead in this comparison, thanks to more features (6 vs 5), availability of a free plan. However, this does not mean Phind is a poor choice — far from it. Phind excels in its own right, particularly for developers searching for code solutions and replacing Stack Overflow.\n\nOur recommendation: if you value strong test generation, go with Qodo. If web-search backed answers matters more to you, Phind is the way to go. Either way, both are solid platforms that have earned their place in the market."}]]}]
